{"ts":"2026-06-27T00:56:55.324Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing Implementation Gap Structure**\n\nI'm now focusing on the structure of the implementation gap report. I'm prioritizing the inclusion of a detailed file inspection log within the report. It is necessary to detail all files read or checked. This also involves defining a clear reporting framework. I'm assessing various methods to present the necessary data concisely and accessibly.\n\n\n**Defining Missing Features**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the identification of missing features across various areas. My current focus involves listing unimplemented routes under `/app/`, especially critical aspects like admin dashboards and login functionalities. I'm also cataloging the required components, such as local authentication switchers and role switching interfaces. I'm evaluating the security and performance risks and considering recommended implementation steps.\n\n\n**Identifying Critical Functionality**\n\nI'm now identifying critical functionality. I have determined that we need dedicated routes for `/login` and `/admin`, with supporting sub-routes within `/admin` like `/admin/clients` and `/admin/users`. I'm evaluating mock authentication for login. I'm also now thinking of the structure for an app shell and logged-in user experience. This necessitates a separate dashboard shell to replace the global `Header`.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Role Switching**\n\nI'm now focusing on role-switching features, especially a dynamic switcher. I need to simulate different user roles effectively within the app. I'm focusing on creating an accessible \"Developer Preview Panel\" that supports role toggling. I must ensure proper authentication state management and consistent display, which requires secure storage implementation. I must design the mock authentication and route protection so it is accessible.\n\n\n**Defining Access Control**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the implementation of robust access control mechanisms. I've pinpointed the lack of route-guarding previews for key sections like `/portal/control-center`, `/client`, and `/client/control-center`. I'm focusing on implementing a client-side middleware or route wrapper. It must check for mock sessions and redirect to `/login` if none exist. I must show an \"Access Denied\" lock screen for unauthorized attempts.\n\n**Enhancing Client Dashboard**\n\nI am now focusing on refining the Client Portal Dashboard. My initial assessments have pinpointed the need to improve from basic static panels to a high-fidelity overview. This includes beautiful telemetry charts, system health summaries, and dynamic notification feeds. I need to integrate actionable widgets, active agent counters, and token quota meters to deliver a more premium user experience.\n\n**Designing Interactive Project Wizards**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on project management. I've recognized the need to move beyond simple table listings of projects. I'm focusing on building interactive project creation wizards and comprehensive project detail pages. I'm prioritizing the implementation of user-friendly interfaces to enhance user experience.\n\n\n**Expanding Project Data**\n\nI'm now prioritizing interactive data within project views. I'm focusing on implementing detailed drill-downs, node topology DAG graphs, and environment toggle controls to enhance the understanding of project structure and its environment. I'm evaluating the UI elements necessary to display these details clearly and concisely.\n\nI'm now diving into the AI Operations section and am finding a simple table of agents is limiting. I require interactive agent creation, agent prompt overrides, state inspectors, live trace/step log viewers, and thread allocation controls. In the documents section, the simple list of static docs needs an upload area, folder system, and cryptographic signature verification viewer. The billing area lacks payment configuration, usage simulators, and real-time ledger logs. Finally, the Support area also needs a better implementation.\n\n\n**Expanding Ticket Features**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the enhancements to the Support area and the ticket system. I'm focusing on features such as a detailed thread view and an agent helper assistant, which will address issues before requiring a ticket. I'm also planning to implement live status tracking, including \"Submitted,\" \"In Review,\" and \"Resolved\" statuses.\n\n**Enhancing Analytics Views**\n\nI'm now focusing on refining the Analytics section. I've noted that the initial SVG sparkline graph showing real-time data and node lists needs expansion. I'm implementing complex telemetry controls with filterable date ranges, aggregated token spend metrics, detailed latency charts, and mock export buttons.\n\n**Defining Governance Requirements**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on defining requirements for the Governance section. The current hardcoded compliance policies must be expanded. I'm focusing on adding a policy editor, audit logs, real-time alert triggers, a simulation tool, and a sovereign keys manager.\n\n**Developing Settings Framework**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the implementation of the Settings section, which is currently missing. I'm focusing on developing a Settings UI that includes security settings, such as passkey configuration and SSO integration, and API key generation.\n\n\n**Defining Admin Capabilities**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the Admin Dashboard. I'm focusing on defining the crucial components: total active clients, aggregate compute load, support queue status, governance alerts, and active node clusters. I'm also cataloging the need for an admin interface for client management. This includes capabilities to create, edit, suspend, upgrade client organizations, configure multi-tenant quotas, and provision sovereign hardware enclaves. Also, the user management view, project management view and documents admin view are required.\n\n\n**Expanding Admin Dashboards**\n\nI'm now focusing on admin dashboards. I've pinpointed several critical missing views: billing management, support ticket assignment, global analytics, and governance controls. Each dashboard requires specific functionalities like subscription pricing management, ticket assignment, usage statistics, and compliance guardrails. I'm also planning to implement an activity feed and a notification system for real-time system updates and alerts.\n\n\n**Integrating Search Features**\n\nI'm now prioritizing the integration of the search functionality and command center throughout the internal portal elements. I'm focusing on enabling search for active projects, invoices, and agents directly from the command center. I also need to provide jump-routing and trigger terminal console states from the command center.\n\n\n\n"}}
